Section 1:
SR 13 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 13 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 13(By Senators Clements, Oliverio, Smith (Mr. President), Azinger, Barrett, Bartlett, Boley, Chapman, Charnock, Deeds, Fuller, Garcia, Grady, Hamilton, Hart, Helton, Jeffries, Martin, Maynard, Morris, Phillips, Queen, Roberts, Rose, Rucker, Stuart, Takubo, Tarr, Taylor, Thorne, Weld, Willis, Woelfel, and Woodrum)[Introduced February 25, 2025] Memorializing the life of Wanda Porterfield Casto, wife, mother, grandmother, sister, and dedicated public servant.Whereas, Wanda Porterfield Casto was born the daughter of Gordon Taylor (G.T.) and Annabelle (Snead) Porterfield, in Bluefield, West Virginia, in 1943; andWhereas, The Casto family moved to Charleston where Wanda graduated from Charleston High School in 1961; andWhereas, During her working years, Wanda Porterfield Casto’s organizational disposition and secretarial skills allowed her to excel in her career. Her employments included FMC – Ordinance Division; Office Manager for Rogelio T. Lim, MD; part-time bookkeeper for Lynn Gianola, CPA; part-time secretary for her beloved husband, David Casto, Appraiser, for almost 55 years; and Whereas, Wanda Porterfield Casto dedicated herself to the West Virginia Senate for 34 years as a part-time Secretary/Administrative Assistant, where she worked for several senators on both sides of the aisle, imparting her institutional knowledge on newer members and staff and always displaying her masterful organizational and task-driven skills; andWhereas, Wanda Porterfield Casto considered the West Virginia Senate her “Happy Place”, where she loved those who she worked with and treasured the connections she made throughout her career under the dome; andWhereas, Wanda Porterfield Casto was a loyal and faithful believer in Jesus Christ.  Wanda was an active member of Cross Lanes Bible Church for nearly 40 years and an active member of Bible Center Church the last 15 years; andWhereas, Wanda Porterfield Casto deeply loved and cared for her family, current and past neighbors, co-workers, church families, and anyone who crossed her path. Her daily words of encouragement or a shared verse brought warmness to others; andWhereas, Wanda Porterfield Casto was married to her beloved husband, David, for 56 years, with whom she shared the joy of having a daughter, Lisa (Chris); her granddaughter, Abbigail (Mark) Davidson; grandson, Austin Michels; great-grandsons, Peyton and Crew Davidson; granddaughter and great-grandchildren of the heart, Leslie, Ian, and Devon Southern; twin sister, Linda Kesting; sisters, Katy Lim and Jackie Rollyson; and so many special nieces, nephews, and many close and special friends; andWhereas, Sadly, Wanda Porterfield Casto passed away at her home on May 20, 2024, bringing an end to a life that was dedicated to public service and service to the Lord; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby memorializes the life of Wanda Porterfield Casto, wife, mother, grandmother, sister, and dedicated public servant; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Senate hereby extends its deepest sympathies to the family of Wanda Porterfield Casto; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the family of Wanda Porterfield Casto. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


